        <name>Seng’an Daoyi</name>
    </subject>
    <abstract>This the first article that correctly reads "Seng’an Daoyi" instead of family name "An" and
        personal name "Daoyi". Zhang Weiran proves that "Seng’an" is the name of the monk, and monks’ names
        could be abbreviated by only using the second character. Furthermore, there are many monks’ names with
        the character "An" as the first part of the name. Monks’ names consist of two parts: The first part is
        called 名, the second 字.</abstract>
